5. Deployment Automation (IaC)
Objective: Define and deploy your application's infrastructure as code using Terraform.

Prerequisite: Install Terraform and the Google Cloud SDK.

Lab: Deploy to Cloud Run with Terraform
Authenticate: Run gcloud auth application-default login to allow Terraform to use your credentials.

Create main.tf: In a new directory, create a main.tf file. This code defines a Cloud Run service that uses the public "hello" image.

Terraform

terraform {
  required_providers {
    google = {
      source  = "hashicorp/google"
      version = "5.34.0"
    }
  }
}

provider "google" {
  project = "YOUR_PROJECT_ID" # Replace with your Project ID
  region  = "us-central1"
}

# 1. Define the Cloud Run service
resource "google_cloud_run_service" "default" {
  name     = "hello-terraform"
  location = "us-central1"

  template {
    spec {
      containers {
        image = "us-docker.pkg.dev/cloudrun/container/hello"
      }
    }
  }
}

# 2. Define the IAM policy to allow public access
resource "google_cloud_run_service_iam_member" "noauth" {
  service  = google_cloud_run_service.default.name
  location = google_cloud_run_service.default.location
  role     = "roles/run.invoker"
  member   = "allUsers"
}

# 3. Output the URL
output "service_url" {
  value = google_cloud_run_service.default.status[0].url
}
Initialize: In your terminal, in the same directory, run:

Bash

terraform init
Plan: See what Terraform will create:

Bash

terraform plan
Apply: Build the infrastructure:

Bash

terraform apply
Type yes when prompted.

Verify: After it finishes, Terraform will output the service_url. Open this URL in your browser to see your app.

Destroy: To clean up, run:

Bash

terraform destroy
